    q: "What size gaming monitor should I get?",
    a: "27 inches at 1440p is the most popular gaming setup, and for good reason — it's the ideal pixel density for desktop viewing distance (2-3 feet). 24-inch 1080p is preferred by competitive esports players for tighter field of view. 32-inch works best at 4K resolution to maintain sharpness. Ultrawides at 34 inches are excellent for immersion but require more desk space and GPU power."
