    <section class="content-section">
      <p>The gaming monitor market has never been better — or more confusing. OLED panels have dropped to attainable prices, 4K 240Hz exists, and you can get a solid 1440p 165Hz monitor for $200. The problem is figuring out which specs actually matter for how you play.</p>
      <p>We evaluated each monitor on image quality, motion clarity, input lag, color accuracy, build quality, and value. Whether you need a curved gaming monitor for immersion or the best monitor for gaming at a competitive level, we've tested the options and picked clear winners.</p>

